  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIt looks like the `validator account create` command will not create any new accounts if the target directory is empty.\r\n\r\n`mkdir empty-keystore-dir`\r\n\r\n` ./validator accounts create --keystore-path=./empty-keystore-dir --password=ok`\r\n\r\noutput:\r\n\r\n[2020-05-17 12:39:32] FATAL main: Could not create validator at path: ./keystore error=path \"./keystore\" does not exist\r\n\r\nExpecting:\r\nINFO accounts: Account creation complete!  ....\r\n\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nNot tested on any previous version\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\n<!--\r\nPlease let us know how we can reproduce this issue. Include the exact method you used to run Prysm along with any flags used in your beacon chain and/or validator. Make sure you don't upload any confidential files or private keys.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n<code>\r\n[2020-05-17 12:39:32] FATAL main: Could not create validator at path: ./keystore error=path \"./keystore\" does not exist\r\n</code>\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\n x86_64 GNU/Linux 5.4\r\n  go1.14.3\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nThe latest pulled from master just the other day\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Further info**\r\n\r\nIt looks like the bug is in validator/accounts/account.go:124 in the `Exists` func\r\n\r\n```// Exists checks if a validator account at a given keystore path exists.\r\nfunc Exists(keystorePath string) (bool, error) {\r\n\t/* #nosec */\r\n\tf, err := os.Open(keystorePath)\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\treturn false, nil\r\n\t}\r\n\tdefer func() {\r\n\t\tif err := f.Close(); err != nil {\r\n\t\t\tlog.Fatal(err)\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}()\r\n\r\n\t_, err = f.Readdirnames(1) // Or f.Readdir(1)\r\n\tif err == io.EOF {\r\n\t\treturn false, nil\r\n\t}\r\n\treturn true, err\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n***Additional comment\r\n\r\nIt seems like `Exists` function expects at least one file or sub-directory to be present, and it will return an error if the keystore dir is empty even if it exists. \r\n\r\nI could gladly submit a PR with the following proposed fixes:\r\n\r\n1. remove the following code from account.go\r\n\r\n<code>\r\n        _, err = f.Readdirnames(1) // Or f.Readdir(1)\r\n\tif err == io.EOF {\r\n\t\treturn false, nil\r\n\t}\r\n</code>\r\n\r\n2. add a test case\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks\r\n\r\nEdit: formatting",
